1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:02:40,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.li Support Admin)

2
00:03:29,745 --> 00:03:30,635
Perfect timing.

3
00:03:30,659 --> 00:03:35,918
You want to know what happened
to those missing students, right?

4
00:03:35,943 --> 00:03:38,028
Lorelei. Lorelei, are you okay?

5
00:03:38,999 --> 00:03:40,000
Lorelei.

6
00:03:40,918 --> 00:03:41,961
Loki!

7
00:03:49,385 --> 00:03:52,697
Now we know
someone's working for Moriarty.

8
00:03:52,721 --> 00:03:55,283
I have a student, Stein Alberts.

9
00:03:55,307 --> 00:03:56,660
When did anyone last see him?

10
00:03:56,684 --> 00:03:58,310
This place has a rodent problem.

11
00:03:58,519 --> 00:03:59,854
If you can hear me

12
00:04:00,604 --> 00:04:02,439
knock, so we know where you are.

13
00:04:04,316 --> 00:04:06,026
I wish it was always like this.

14
00:04:06,527 --> 00:04:08,320
Before the tragedy occurs,

15
00:04:08,529 --> 00:04:10,072
we can stop it.

16
00:04:10,239 --> 00:04:11,365
Let's be honest.

17
00:04:12,575 --> 00:04:14,760
We both know who's behind this incident.

18
00:04:16,912 --> 00:04:17,955
Are you okay?

19
00:04:19,707 --> 00:04:23,210
Does it bother you
that M may be tied to Stein's case?

20
00:04:28,966 --> 00:04:30,025
You know,

21
00:04:30,050 --> 00:04:33,596
I'd rather you answer sarcastically
than like that.

22
00:04:34,305 --> 00:04:36,515
I don't know what's going on in your head.

23
00:04:37,433 --> 00:04:40,537
I thought you were smart enough
to understand my distress

24
00:04:40,561 --> 00:04:43,731
at the fact that my arch enemy
was involved in the case.

25
00:04:44,857 --> 00:04:46,567
Do I still need to explain that?

26
00:04:46,901 --> 00:04:49,504
I just wanted to hear it directly from you,

27
00:04:49,528 --> 00:04:50,821
even if I already knew.

28
00:04:51,864 --> 00:04:55,117
Sometimes it helps to say how you feel

29
00:04:55,284 --> 00:04:56,952
instead of keeping it in.

30
00:04:58,329 --> 00:05:01,457
Sorry, I didn't mean
to overhear your argument.

31
00:05:02,124 --> 00:05:03,292
It's okay.

32
00:05:03,792 --> 00:05:06,253
Rosetta, wait. Why are you here?

33
00:05:06,295 --> 00:05:07,880
Do you have a case to bring up?

34
00:05:08,047 --> 00:05:10,674
Nope. I have a different agenda today.

35
00:05:10,966 --> 00:05:12,635
Oh, okay. Have a seat.

36
00:05:12,801 --> 00:05:13,801
Thank you.

37
00:05:14,220 --> 00:05:15,220
Agenda?

38
00:05:15,471 --> 00:05:18,474
What? Another boring ghost hunt?

39
00:05:19,683 --> 00:05:21,685
Or do you have something
more thrilling to offer?

40
00:05:23,020 --> 00:05:24,897
I want to join the Q.E.D. Club!

41
00:05:27,358 --> 00:05:30,402
I saw how cool you guys were yesterday.

42
00:05:30,569 --> 00:05:32,780
So I decided to join too.

43
00:05:32,863 --> 00:05:36,158
You still have space
for one or two more members, right?

44
00:05:36,867 --> 00:05:42,539
Well, I'm just the Vice President,
so you can review her application.

45
00:05:45,334 --> 00:05:47,670
We don't take just anyone
as a club member.

46
00:05:48,295 --> 00:05:49,295
Loki!

47
00:05:50,506 --> 00:05:52,675
Especially, the likes of you.

48
00:05:55,219 --> 00:05:57,054
The likes of me?

49
00:05:58,222 --> 00:06:00,307
Why? What's wrong with me?

50
00:06:01,517 --> 00:06:02,601
First of all

51
00:06:03,936 --> 00:06:05,104
you believe in ghosts.

52
00:06:06,647 --> 00:06:08,065
We can't have someone

53
00:06:08,357 --> 00:06:11,110
who believes in nonsense.

54
00:06:13,654 --> 00:06:15,656
You have to have something to believe in!

55
00:06:17,700 --> 00:06:19,326
You know what? Then, don't!

56
00:06:19,451 --> 00:06:21,370
Drop it! Your loss!

57
00:06:21,578 --> 00:06:22,746
Rosetta!

58
00:06:23,998 --> 00:06:26,500
Loki, why did you have to be such a jerk?

59
00:06:27,418 --> 00:06:30,421
You could've said it nicely without insults.

60
00:06:31,463 --> 00:06:33,507
We don't need excess baggage in the club.

61
00:06:34,675 --> 00:06:36,093
How would she contribute?

62
00:06:36,802 --> 00:06:37,802
Watch?

63
00:06:38,304 --> 00:06:39,430
Clap?

64
00:06:40,431 --> 00:06:42,308
Just say, "Cool"?

65
00:06:44,059 --> 00:06:46,895
Every member should have a role to play.

66
00:06:47,771 --> 00:06:48,771
Okay?

67
00:06:49,064 --> 00:06:51,734
Then why did you force me to join here?

68
00:06:52,443 --> 00:06:56,447
I'm not even good
at investigation or deduction.

69
00:07:00,868 --> 00:07:02,679
I asked you specifically

70
00:07:02,703 --> 00:07:05,247
to be a chronicler
of the club's adventures.

71
00:07:05,789 --> 00:07:06,874
So don't worry,

72
00:07:07,041 --> 00:07:10,127
your role benefits the club,
even if you're not that good.

73
00:07:11,879 --> 00:07:13,297
But Rosalinda

74
00:07:14,048 --> 00:07:15,049
nothing.

75
00:07:15,632 --> 00:07:16,884
It's Rosetta!

76
00:07:16,967 --> 00:07:19,636
And another thing, Loki,
it's not really because...

77
00:07:23,640 --> 00:07:24,641
Let's go!

78
00:07:28,437 --> 00:07:30,564
Oh, my gosh! This is so gory!

79
00:07:46,538 --> 00:07:48,415
It seems like we have a new case to solve.

80
00:07:57,524 --> 00:07:59,443
♪ Shadows ♪

81
00:08:00,202 --> 00:08:02,913
♪ in the dark are crawling. ♪

82
00:08:03,889 --> 00:08:07,911
♪ Keeping watch and barring your way. ♪

83
00:08:07,935 --> 00:08:11,480
♪ As if the line could not be crossed. ♪

84
00:08:12,138 --> 00:08:15,692
♪ To every scream and every tremor. ♪

85
00:08:15,717 --> 00:08:18,819
♪ These walls remain the only witness. ♪

86
00:08:18,844 --> 00:08:21,804
♪ Every noise is etched in here. ♪

87
00:08:21,829 --> 00:08:26,334
♪ Like fire and ammunition
for your memory. ♪

88
00:08:27,597 --> 00:08:29,724
♪ Heed the warnings. ♪

89
00:08:31,010 --> 00:08:33,387
♪ The threats poised to strike. ♪

90
00:08:34,404 --> 00:08:38,261
♪ For this world ♪

91
00:08:38,835 --> 00:08:41,462
♪ is not what you imagined. ♪

92
00:08:41,487 --> 00:08:43,947
♪ Heed the warnings. ♪

93
00:08:44,738 --> 00:08:47,310
♪ Open up your eyes. ♪

94
00:08:48,251 --> 00:08:51,797
♪ For this world ♪

95
00:08:52,846 --> 00:08:55,261
♪ is not what you imagined. ♪

96
00:08:55,286 --> 00:09:00,124
♪ Heed the warnings. ♪

97
00:09:23,343 --> 00:09:24,636
Catherine Del Rosario.

98
00:09:24,928 --> 00:09:27,115
But we might not need your help anymore

99
00:09:27,139 --> 00:09:30,767
since this is being treated
as a suspected suicide.

100
00:09:35,856 --> 00:09:39,985
What are the chances
that an individual taking their own life

101
00:09:40,369 --> 00:09:41,620
by jumping off a height

102
00:09:42,235 --> 00:09:44,529
would land face up on the ground?

103
00:09:45,991 --> 00:09:47,868
Good point. Good point.

104
00:09:48,952 --> 00:09:50,037
She didn't jump.

105
00:09:51,747 --> 00:09:52,789
She was pushed.

106
00:09:55,834 --> 00:09:57,169
Chief, may I?

107
00:10:14,675 --> 00:10:16,719
The perfume on the handkerchief
smells like a man's.

108
00:10:17,606 --> 00:10:20,233
It couldn't be the victim's,
it could belong to someone else.

109
00:10:22,152 --> 00:10:24,541
Looks like she grabbed this
from the one who pushed her.

110
00:10:26,573 --> 00:10:27,573
Sir.

111
00:10:29,117 --> 00:10:30,369
This isn't suicide.

112
00:10:31,578 --> 00:10:32,579
This is murder.

113
00:10:34,248 --> 00:10:35,749
And thanks to that handkerchief.

114
00:10:38,418 --> 00:10:39,711
I think I know who did it.

115
00:10:51,974 --> 00:10:54,226
Will this ever end?

116
00:10:55,018 --> 00:10:58,414
No matter how many corpses I see,
I'll never get used to it.

117
00:10:58,438 --> 00:11:00,774
I'll never get used to it.

118
00:11:05,529 --> 00:11:06,529
So

119
00:11:06,989 --> 00:11:08,490
What do you think about the case?

120
00:11:09,241 --> 00:11:10,701
Is it murder or suicide?

121
00:11:11,994 --> 00:11:13,537
Why are you still asking me?

122
00:11:13,996 --> 00:11:15,636
Haven't you already come to a conclusion?

123
00:11:16,415 --> 00:11:21,003
Besides, you said
I'm not good at deduction.

124
00:11:21,628 --> 00:11:23,714
And I'm just the club's chronicler anyway.

125
00:11:25,173 --> 00:11:26,717
I still want to know your opinion,

126
00:11:27,426 --> 00:11:29,011
and if you agree with my deduction.

127
00:11:30,220 --> 00:11:32,180
I'd be surprised if you think otherwise.

128
00:11:35,392 --> 00:11:36,392
Well, I.

129
00:11:37,644 --> 00:11:38,979
I think the chief is right.

130
00:11:39,730 --> 00:11:41,315
Catherine ended her own life.

131
00:11:41,815 --> 00:11:44,151
Looks like we're looking at this
from different angles.

132
00:11:45,777 --> 00:11:47,654
Are you saying that just to spite me?

133
00:11:48,488 --> 00:11:49,924
Is this you trying to prove

134
00:11:49,948 --> 00:11:52,951
that you can also be a detective
on your own merits?

135
00:11:54,745 --> 00:11:58,498
Now that I've told you my opinion,
you're just contradicting me.

136
00:11:59,458 --> 00:12:01,058
You shouldn't even be asking me anymore.

137
00:12:02,210 --> 00:12:04,880
Why do you think your opinion
is more valid than mine?

138
00:12:06,590 --> 00:12:07,799
Let's compare notes.

139
00:12:13,305 --> 00:12:15,057
The victim was smiling when she fell.

140
00:12:16,308 --> 00:12:20,562
If she was pushed,
whether intentionally or by accident,

141
00:12:21,146 --> 00:12:23,190
shouldn't her expression show surprise?

142
00:12:27,611 --> 00:12:29,154
You're making a grand assumption

143
00:12:29,863 --> 00:12:33,408
out of a tiny,
and probably insignificant detail.

144
00:12:34,034 --> 00:12:36,286
Maybe she's just happy
with the guy she's with.

145
00:12:36,745 --> 00:12:38,664
Not knowing he was going to kill her,

146
00:12:39,247 --> 00:12:40,415
which is why she smiled.

147
00:12:41,291 --> 00:12:43,061
Besides, how can you explain

148
00:12:43,085 --> 00:12:44,878
she's holding someone else's handkerchief?

149
00:12:48,882 --> 00:12:49,882
You're right!

150
00:12:50,384 --> 00:12:54,513
This handkerchief might be the clue
to finding out who pushed her.

151
00:12:55,347 --> 00:12:58,517
Or maybe
that's just what she wants us to think.

152
00:13:00,310 --> 00:13:03,689
Oh, so you're not giving up, huh?

153
00:13:04,564 --> 00:13:05,564
Go on

154
00:13:05,941 --> 00:13:07,609
entertain me with your theory.

155
00:13:08,360 --> 00:13:11,071
Maybe she wants it
to look like it was murder.

156
00:13:11,380 --> 00:13:13,674
To frame the guy she was with.

157
00:13:13,699 --> 00:13:16,952
But the police declared
that the cause is self-inflicted.

158
00:13:17,619 --> 00:13:21,748
If no one pointed out that it was murder,
her plan would fail.

159
00:13:22,249 --> 00:13:24,185
Maybe she's counting on someone

160
00:13:24,209 --> 00:13:27,212
with superb deductive skills
to disprove it.

161
00:13:27,838 --> 00:13:29,089
You mean someone like me?

162
00:13:34,177 --> 00:13:37,013
Oh, what's up?
What's your theory on what happened?

163
00:13:38,765 --> 00:13:41,935
Chief, it seems like Lorelei and I
have different opinions.

164
00:13:43,228 --> 00:13:47,733
I'm afraid we have to pursue two angles
of this case separately.

165
00:13:49,025 --> 00:13:51,611
And we also have to invite
the owner of the handkerchief.

166
00:13:56,700 --> 00:13:59,828
This is going to be
an interesting deduction showdown.

167
00:14:00,245 --> 00:14:02,873
And I'm gonna prove to you
that you're wrong.

168
00:14:03,786 --> 00:14:04,787
Seriously?

169
00:14:05,292 --> 00:14:10,130
Is it more important for you
to prove me wrong than know the truth?

170
00:14:10,380 --> 00:14:13,884
As if someone's death
is just a game to you.

171
00:14:24,436 --> 00:14:26,730
Guys, this is Leo Dacillo.

172
00:14:27,189 --> 00:14:28,774
The boyfriend of the deceased.

173
00:14:28,857 --> 00:14:29,941
Ex-boyfriend.

174
00:14:30,942 --> 00:14:32,782
Cath and I have been broken up
for a long time.

175
00:14:33,361 --> 00:14:34,571
What do you need from me?

176
00:14:36,615 --> 00:14:37,866
Is this handkerchief yours?

177
00:14:38,533 --> 00:14:39,533
Yes, it's mine.

178
00:14:40,243 --> 00:14:42,163
But that handkerchief's
been missing for a while.

179
00:14:42,621 --> 00:14:44,122
Catherine was holding this,

180
00:14:44,623 --> 00:14:46,124
when she fell down and died.

181
00:14:47,667 --> 00:14:48,667
Hold on.

182
00:14:49,127 --> 00:14:52,214
Do you think I'm the one
who pushed Catherine to her death?

183
00:14:54,007 --> 00:14:55,550
We're looking at that possibility.

184
00:14:56,301 --> 00:14:59,012
Like I said, that handkerchief's
been missing for a long time!

185
00:15:01,598 --> 00:15:03,598
Catherine and I have been broken up
for two months.

186
00:15:04,392 --> 00:15:08,188
I was the one who broke up with her,
but she still hasn't accepted it.

187
00:15:09,064 --> 00:15:10,064
So

188
00:15:10,690 --> 00:15:11,691
You got fed up.

189
00:15:12,108 --> 00:15:15,195
And in your anger,
you could've pushed her.

190
00:15:16,238 --> 00:15:19,533
Then you made it look like
she jumped on her own, right?

191
00:15:19,783 --> 00:15:21,743
I could never do that!

192
00:15:21,952 --> 00:15:23,203
If you're not guilty,

193
00:15:23,370 --> 00:15:25,413
what were you doing there
in the first place?

194
00:15:25,914 --> 00:15:27,582
Catherine asked to meet me.

195
00:15:28,416 --> 00:15:30,102
She'd been bugging me
with messages for a while,

196
00:15:30,126 --> 00:15:33,171
so I finally agreed just to make her stop.

197
00:15:34,381 --> 00:15:36,675
She said she wanted closure

198
00:15:37,050 --> 00:15:38,343
about our breakup.

199
00:15:38,927 --> 00:15:40,303
When I got there,

200
00:15:41,221 --> 00:15:43,306
she suddenly jumped backward.

201
00:15:44,432 --> 00:15:47,310
I got scared, so I ran.

202
00:16:06,746 --> 00:16:08,248
This is the last time, Catherine.

203
00:16:08,707 --> 00:16:10,250
What more closure do you need?

204
00:16:16,840 --> 00:16:17,924
Catherine?

205
00:16:19,718 --> 00:16:20,886
What's happening to you?

206
00:16:25,974 --> 00:16:27,100
Catherine, no!

207
00:16:38,361 --> 00:16:39,529
Oh, no!

208
00:16:42,198 --> 00:16:43,742
What is happening? What's that?

209
00:16:58,673 --> 00:17:02,010
Your handkerchief
is the evidence we're holding on to.

210
00:17:02,302 --> 00:17:06,056
And the fact that you were the last person
she spoke to before she fell.

211
00:17:06,890 --> 00:17:09,351
If Leo really pushed Catherine,

212
00:17:09,392 --> 00:17:15,857
shouldn't one or both of his hands
have made contact with her skin or clothes?

213
00:17:16,483 --> 00:17:17,484
Right?

214
00:17:18,860 --> 00:17:22,030
Can we confirm that
through fingerprint analysis?

215
00:17:23,073 --> 00:17:25,992
Lifting fingerprints from clothes
is possible,

216
00:17:27,077 --> 00:17:28,203
but difficult.

217
00:17:28,787 --> 00:17:33,917
One way is if the person who pushed her
had sweaty or oily hands.

218
00:17:34,918 --> 00:17:38,630
If VMD picks something up,
palm print analysis is possible.

219
00:17:39,130 --> 00:17:40,173
And with that,

220
00:17:40,840 --> 00:17:43,593
we'll know if someone
really pushed her or not.

221
00:17:44,803 --> 00:17:45,803
VMD?

222
00:17:46,346 --> 00:17:48,974
Vacuum Metal Deposition.

223
00:17:49,265 --> 00:17:54,312
Alright, I'll have
the victim's uniform examined

224
00:17:55,480 --> 00:17:57,458
for palm print impressions

225
00:17:57,482 --> 00:17:59,275
but we don't have the equipment for that.

226
00:18:00,193 --> 00:18:03,488
I'll have it sent to the police
commission's forensics department.

227
00:18:04,239 --> 00:18:08,201
Can we get prints from both of your hands?

228
00:18:09,494 --> 00:18:11,746
If that's what will prove I'm innocent,

229
00:18:12,622 --> 00:18:13,915
then no problem.

230
00:18:16,501 --> 00:18:17,501
Okay.

231
00:18:20,505 --> 00:18:22,257
Wanna bet what the result's gonna be?

232
00:18:22,924 --> 00:18:25,301
This isn't a game, okay?

233
00:18:25,510 --> 00:18:28,763
This kind of situation
shouldn't be turned into a bet.

234
00:18:29,139 --> 00:18:31,391
A human life was lost, Loki.

235
00:18:42,986 --> 00:18:44,279
These are the results.

236
00:18:45,780 --> 00:18:49,784
No palm prints from the suspect
were found on the victim's uniform.

237
00:18:50,201 --> 00:18:51,953
Yes! I knew it!

238
00:18:52,787 --> 00:18:54,539
Sorry. That was too much.

239
00:18:55,248 --> 00:18:57,333
I didn't mean to celebrate, but.

240
00:18:57,792 --> 00:19:02,005
I'm putting this on the blog,
my theory was right, and you were wrong.

241
00:19:02,547 --> 00:19:07,552
So whether you admit it or not,
I can be a detective too.

242
00:19:08,428 --> 00:19:09,428
Of course!

243
00:19:12,140 --> 00:19:13,683
But not on my level.

244
00:19:15,894 --> 00:19:17,270
To be perfectly honest,

245
00:19:18,021 --> 00:19:22,025
I also considered
your suicide-to-frame-someone angle.

246
00:19:23,860 --> 00:19:25,612
But I didn't tell you right away,

247
00:19:26,071 --> 00:19:29,592
because sometimes it helps

248
00:19:29,616 --> 00:19:33,495
when we see things differently
to lets us cover every possibility.

249
00:19:35,497 --> 00:19:36,539
Anyway,

250
00:19:37,540 --> 00:19:39,000
before you gloat or anything,

251
00:19:39,751 --> 00:19:43,856
I just wanted to explain
why I didn't accept Rosario in the club.

252
00:19:43,880 --> 00:19:45,340
It's Rosetta, Loki!

253
00:19:45,465 --> 00:19:47,842
Is it really that hard to remember?

254
00:19:53,431 --> 00:19:54,682
As I was saying

255
00:19:55,809 --> 00:19:58,895
being part of the club and by extension,

256
00:19:59,479 --> 00:20:02,649
being close to me
has proven to be dangerous.

257
00:20:04,150 --> 00:20:06,444
You experienced it last week
when you were abducted.

258
00:20:07,278 --> 00:20:08,947
You became a liability to me.

259
00:20:12,075 --> 00:20:14,327
But don't get me wrong,

260
00:20:15,203 --> 00:20:16,621
I value your presence

261
00:20:17,122 --> 00:20:20,542
particularly when you tried to stop me
from melting that fake janitor.

262
00:20:22,627 --> 00:20:23,878
If you hadn't been there,

263
00:20:24,420 --> 00:20:26,089
I probably would've finished him off.

264
00:20:26,339 --> 00:20:28,550
No! Loki, that's enough!

265
00:20:28,716 --> 00:20:29,716
Please.

266
00:20:30,051 --> 00:20:31,553
Think about this.

267
00:20:32,929 --> 00:20:34,097
So you see.

268
00:20:35,557 --> 00:20:37,559
I can't add another liability.

269
00:20:38,393 --> 00:20:39,894
Unless the applicant,

270
00:20:40,520 --> 00:20:44,232
can protect himself or herself
without my help.

271
00:21:02,250 --> 00:21:04,419
I failed to protect Rhea before.

272
00:21:10,091 --> 00:21:11,926
I don't want that to happen to you.

273
00:21:19,475 --> 00:21:21,227
I understand that.

274
00:21:22,937 --> 00:21:27,483
Can you please try to be
a little bit gentler next time?

275
00:21:28,067 --> 00:21:29,861
You don't have to be rude.

276
00:21:31,779 --> 00:21:33,364
Maybe it's because of M.

277
00:21:34,449 --> 00:21:37,178
Whenever I hear that single letter,

278
00:21:37,202 --> 00:21:41,289
or even the full codename Moriarty,
I get triggered.

279
00:21:43,458 --> 00:21:45,418
I can sometimes lose my cool

280
00:21:46,294 --> 00:21:47,462
because of him.

281
00:21:52,467 --> 00:21:53,509
Anyway,

282
00:21:54,510 --> 00:21:56,304
speaking of that monster

283
00:21:57,889 --> 00:21:59,349
I'll give you something.

284
00:22:00,516 --> 00:22:01,516
Hey.

285
00:22:02,018 --> 00:22:03,603
It's not even my birthday yet.

286
00:22:05,104 --> 00:22:06,189
What's this?

287
00:22:08,274 --> 00:22:10,485
Just open it and see for yourself.

288
00:22:16,658 --> 00:22:18,284
A ball pen?

289
00:22:19,619 --> 00:22:21,287
That's no ordinary pen.

290
00:22:22,455 --> 00:22:26,334
It's a stunning device disguised as a pen
that you can bring anywhere.

291
00:22:27,961 --> 00:22:30,964
I had that made by someone I know
who's great with inventions.

292
00:22:33,508 --> 00:22:34,592
Lorelei

293
00:22:36,844 --> 00:22:41,182
we don't know when Moriarty
or his agents will strike again.

294
00:22:44,143 --> 00:22:46,813
But if and when that time comes,

295
00:22:48,356 --> 00:22:50,400
you can use something to defend yourself.

296
00:22:54,153 --> 00:22:55,238
Thank you.

297
00:22:57,282 --> 00:22:59,075
Even if you can be a little rude,

298
00:22:59,617 --> 00:23:01,786
you're actually really thoughtful.

299
00:23:03,788 --> 00:23:04,789
Anyway,

300
00:23:05,832 --> 00:23:07,125
how do you use this?

301
00:23:08,418 --> 00:23:12,255
Well, all you need to do
is press this button,

302
00:23:12,797 --> 00:23:16,694
and it will generate
a high voltage electrical charge

303
00:23:16,718 --> 00:23:18,511
that can immobilize anyone who...

304
00:23:37,905 --> 00:23:38,905
Sorry.

305
00:23:39,657 --> 00:23:42,952
I didn't know the stun pen
would be that powerful.

306
00:23:45,121 --> 00:23:47,290
Be careful when using the stun pen.

307
00:23:48,499 --> 00:23:50,418
Don't use it on any nonsense.

308
00:23:51,169 --> 00:23:52,462
Okay, fine.

309
00:23:55,423 --> 00:23:56,632
By the way.

310
00:23:58,634 --> 00:24:00,470
I need to visit Rhea's tomb.

311
00:24:02,180 --> 00:24:03,723
It's her birthday next week.

312
00:24:05,183 --> 00:24:06,601
You can come if you want.

313
00:24:07,518 --> 00:24:08,518
Sure.

314
00:24:11,939 --> 00:24:15,586
♪ The silence is deafening ♪

315
00:24:15,610 --> 00:24:17,945
♪ I can't feel you anymore. ♪

316
00:24:18,905 --> 00:24:22,676
♪ Just staring into the distance. ♪

317
00:24:22,700 --> 00:24:24,994
♪ My heart has grown weary. ♪

318
00:24:25,953 --> 00:24:29,308
♪ And now, I face the truth. ♪

319
00:24:29,332 --> 00:24:32,335
♪ That you're really gone. ♪

320
00:24:33,044 --> 00:24:34,337
♪ The question is... ♪

321
00:24:35,254 --> 00:24:38,817
♪ Who will let go first? ♪

322
00:24:38,841 --> 00:24:42,488
♪ Will it be me or you. ♪

323
00:24:42,512 --> 00:24:45,616
♪ To finally end us. ♪

324
00:24:45,640 --> 00:24:49,453
♪ We can't bring back what we had. ♪

325
00:24:49,477 --> 00:24:53,123
♪ Since the line was let go. ♪

326
00:24:53,147 --> 00:24:55,292
♪ Ready to walk away. ♪

327
00:24:55,316 --> 00:24:56,668
♪ It's all been drained. ♪

328
00:24:56,692 --> 00:25:00,089
♪ Our love and tears. ♪

329
00:25:00,113 --> 00:25:03,991
♪ We can't bring back what we had. ♪

330
00:25:07,203 --> 00:25:10,891
♪ The meaning it once held. ♪

331
00:25:10,915 --> 00:25:13,418
♪ The happiness it meant. ♪

332
00:25:14,563 --> 00:25:15,980
♪ This time... ♪

333
00:25:16,005 --> 00:25:19,048
♪ Happy Birthday to you. ♪

334
00:25:19,090 --> 00:25:21,777
♪ Happy Birthday to you. ♪

335
00:25:21,801 --> 00:25:24,571
♪ Happy Birthday, Happy Birthday. ♪

336
00:25:24,595 --> 00:25:26,573
♪ Happy Birthday to you! ♪

337
00:25:26,597 --> 00:25:27,597
Blow.

338
00:25:28,933 --> 00:25:31,227
Did you like my surprise for you?

339
00:25:31,602 --> 00:25:35,314
It's unnecessary
but I appreciate the effort.

340
00:25:35,982 --> 00:25:38,168
I hope you liked the strawberry cake.

341
00:25:38,192 --> 00:25:40,153
I just didn't know what flavor you liked.

342
00:25:41,654 --> 00:25:42,947
Strawberry's fine.

343
00:25:44,073 --> 00:25:45,450
Any cake is fine.

344
00:25:46,165 --> 00:25:47,405
I don't really have a favorite.

345
00:25:48,911 --> 00:25:51,497
Then what cake did you have
on your birthday last year?

346
00:25:52,498 --> 00:25:54,375
I don't celebrate birthdays.

347
00:25:55,462 --> 00:26:00,262
People only invented birthdays
to have an excuse to celebrate,

348
00:26:00,298 --> 00:26:02,884
and for big companies to use it.

349
00:26:03,509 --> 00:26:06,721
Come on. Don't be so pessimistic, okay?

350
00:26:07,054 --> 00:26:09,807
Then my gift for you is wasted.

351
00:26:10,850 --> 00:26:11,850
Here!

352
00:26:12,643 --> 00:26:13,686
Happy birthday!

353
00:26:14,312 --> 00:26:17,231
Just consider this my
friendship gift to you.

354
00:26:17,440 --> 00:26:18,983
- Just accept it.
- Fine.

355
00:26:19,942 --> 00:26:20,837
Thank you.

356
00:26:20,861 --> 00:26:24,322
We should celebrate
your birthday again next year, okay?

357
00:26:24,530 --> 00:26:25,650
That's still a long way off.

358
00:26:25,823 --> 00:26:27,825
We'll be celebrating your birthday first.

359
00:26:29,118 --> 00:26:30,953
If you remember the date.

360
00:26:33,331 --> 00:26:35,082
Come on, look at the cake.

361
00:26:36,876 --> 00:26:37,187
Rhea must be so special to you.

362
00:26:37,211 --> 00:26:40,379
Rhea must be so special to you.

363
00:26:42,465 --> 00:26:45,944
Since the line was let go.

364
00:26:45,968 --> 00:26:48,197
Ready to walk away.

365
00:26:48,221 --> 00:26:49,698
It's all been drained.

366
00:26:49,722 --> 00:26:52,868
Our love and tears.

367
00:26:52,892 --> 00:26:56,604
We can't bring back what we had.

368
00:26:58,814 --> 00:27:01,108
Who will let go?

369
00:27:01,317 --> 00:27:02,317
Let's go.

370
00:27:02,693 --> 00:27:04,046
Who will let go?

371
00:27:04,070 --> 00:27:06,072
Who will let go?

372
00:27:07,114 --> 00:27:11,327
We can't bring back what we had.

373
00:27:24,799 --> 00:27:26,551
What the hell are you doing here?

374
00:27:27,051 --> 00:27:30,596
You really have the nerve to come here
after everything that happened?

375
00:27:31,222 --> 00:27:34,392
And you even brought the next person
whom you will send to the grave?

376
00:27:35,434 --> 00:27:37,186
I didn't come here to trade barbs.

377
00:27:37,895 --> 00:27:40,356
I came here to honor Rhea's memory.

378
00:27:40,690 --> 00:27:43,526
And I hope you remember all your sins too.

379
00:27:44,068 --> 00:27:47,738
You must never forget the price
Rhea had to pay for being close to you.

380
00:27:48,239 --> 00:27:49,490
I know you hate me,

381
00:27:50,658 --> 00:27:53,995
but, please,
save your anger for another day.

382
00:27:54,537 --> 00:27:57,540
- Hate? I despise you!
- We're leaving.

383
00:27:58,165 --> 00:27:59,250
Don't worry.

384
00:27:59,834 --> 00:28:03,588
You can pay your respects
without getting annoyed by my presence.

385
00:28:05,840 --> 00:28:07,008
See you at school.

386
00:28:15,808 --> 00:28:18,978
Why does Maggie hate you to the bone?

387
00:28:20,479 --> 00:28:22,481
Rhea was more than just a friend to her.

388
00:28:23,399 --> 00:28:25,234
She treated her like a sister.

389
00:28:26,277 --> 00:28:29,280
She warned us
not to involve ourselves with Moriarty.

390
00:28:30,114 --> 00:28:31,449
But I didn't listen.

391
00:28:32,158 --> 00:28:33,618
And soon after,

392
00:28:34,577 --> 00:28:35,828
Rhea was killed.

393
00:28:36,787 --> 00:28:38,497
That's why she blames me.

394
00:28:40,416 --> 00:28:43,878
And she reminds me about it
every opportunity she gets.

395
00:28:49,759 --> 00:28:51,719
Do you think she'll ever forgive you?

396
00:28:54,639 --> 00:28:56,015
Only time can tell.

397
00:29:04,940 --> 00:29:06,942
Wait, did you bring
the stun pen I gave you?

398
00:29:07,276 --> 00:29:09,612
- I brought it.
- Okay. Good.

399
00:29:10,154 --> 00:29:12,299
- It can be.
- What's that?

400
00:29:12,323 --> 00:29:14,784
- Oh, my Gosh!
- What's that?

401
00:29:16,369 --> 00:29:18,055
- What's that?
- Another dead body?

402
00:29:18,079 --> 00:29:20,665
- Oh, my God. It's a person?
- Gosh, come on!

403
00:29:22,166 --> 00:29:24,061
- So scary!
- Yeah, I know!

404
00:29:24,085 --> 00:29:27,004
Oh, my God, there's really
a serial killer in this school.

405
00:29:36,138 --> 00:29:37,532
Did you see where it came from?

406
00:29:37,556 --> 00:29:38,766
From the 5th floor.

407
00:29:40,309 --> 00:29:42,579
- Nothing, really.
- I don't wanna know, but...

408
00:29:42,603 --> 00:29:44,480
Yes, right. It's so bad.

409
00:29:46,482 --> 00:29:48,335
Did any of you see what happened?

410
00:29:48,359 --> 00:29:49,628
- No.
- No.

411
00:29:49,652 --> 00:29:50,629
- Do you know anything?
- No.

412
00:29:50,653 --> 00:29:51,922
- What about you?
- No.

413
00:29:51,946 --> 00:29:53,298
- No.
- Nothing.

414
00:29:53,322 --> 00:29:56,033
- Did any of you see what happened?
- No one.

415
00:29:57,326 --> 00:29:58,369
Me.

416
00:30:00,329 --> 00:30:01,497
Your name, please?

417
00:30:01,997 --> 00:30:03,416
Daniel Geronimo.

418
00:30:05,584 --> 00:30:09,088
Justin Ruiz was my friend,
the guy who jumped.

419
00:30:11,298 --> 00:30:12,758
Can you tell us what happened?

420
00:30:14,510 --> 00:30:17,930
If I'd known he was going to jump,
I would've stopped him right away.

421
00:30:18,389 --> 00:30:22,268
I don't know what went through his mind
that made him do that.

422
00:30:46,208 --> 00:30:47,543
It's still warm.

423
00:30:53,174 --> 00:30:54,633
And it smells like tea.

424
00:31:17,990 --> 00:31:20,159
Did he drink something before jumping?

425
00:31:20,659 --> 00:31:24,121
I just found him here at the edge,
looking down.

426
00:31:25,164 --> 00:31:27,333
I didn't see him holding anything.

427
00:31:28,501 --> 00:31:32,755
I didn't see anyone else besides him.

428
00:31:37,176 --> 00:31:38,469
Strange.

429
00:31:40,721 --> 00:31:41,806
Lorelei,

430
00:31:42,389 --> 00:31:44,058
the teacup's still warm.

431
00:31:44,850 --> 00:31:47,019
If he really had nothing with him
when he went up,

432
00:31:47,561 --> 00:31:49,772
then someone must've placed the cup here

433
00:31:50,105 --> 00:31:52,316
and made him drink the tea.

434
00:31:52,942 --> 00:31:54,109
But why?

435
00:31:56,862 --> 00:31:57,862
Chief.

436
00:32:01,075 --> 00:32:02,451
This is happening way too often.

437
00:32:03,410 --> 00:32:06,097
Chief, we need a fingerprint analysis,

438
00:32:06,121 --> 00:32:10,209
and we need to find out what kind of tea
the suspect made him drink.

439
00:32:11,418 --> 00:32:14,463
It looks like she and Catherine
had the same cause of death.

440
00:32:15,047 --> 00:32:19,552
We don't need your help anymore.
Leave this investigation to us.

441
00:32:20,678 --> 00:32:21,971
Okay, Chief.

442
00:32:27,810 --> 00:32:28,120
Justin Ruiz is my classmate.

443
00:32:28,144 --> 00:32:30,455
Justin Ruiz is my classmate.

444
00:32:30,479 --> 00:32:34,167
I know him.
He's not the type to hurt himself.

445
00:32:34,191 --> 00:32:36,628
Justin's a very confident guy.

446
00:32:36,652 --> 00:32:38,505
A lot of people like him,

447
00:32:38,529 --> 00:32:41,049
especially since he's on the school's
basketball varsity team.

448
00:32:41,073 --> 00:32:45,804
Justin was always cheerful,
even in his social media posts.

449
00:32:45,828 --> 00:32:48,306
He was especially looking forward
to the championship game.

450
00:32:48,330 --> 00:32:48,914
You know,

451
00:32:49,164 --> 00:32:53,085
I've been reading all the comments
about what happened to Justin.

452
00:32:53,586 --> 00:32:57,506
They all say
he'd never do that to himself.

453
00:32:58,007 --> 00:33:00,050
I interviewed his classmates as well,

454
00:33:01,302 --> 00:33:03,178
and they said the exact same thing.

455
00:33:04,638 --> 00:33:06,181
So does that mean

456
00:33:06,640 --> 00:33:08,309
foul play is possible?

457
00:33:08,809 --> 00:33:12,813
Should we be suspicious
of the guy we talked to earlier?

458
00:33:13,105 --> 00:33:14,105
Who?

459
00:33:14,189 --> 00:33:16,692
From that David guy?

460
00:33:16,984 --> 00:33:18,152
Daniel!

461
00:33:18,652 --> 00:33:23,073
The one who said
he tried to stop Justin from jumping.

462
00:33:24,992 --> 00:33:29,079
But eye witnesses said
that the victim jumped by himself.

463
00:33:29,163 --> 00:33:32,666
If he pushed him,
someone should've seen it.

464
00:33:33,125 --> 00:33:34,126
Unless,

465
00:33:34,585 --> 00:33:38,714
he used some magic contraption
to make him fall.

466
00:33:39,840 --> 00:33:43,093
But there's nothing suspicious
from where he jumped.

467
00:33:47,723 --> 00:33:49,224
Is this the Q.E.D. Club?

468
00:33:50,017 --> 00:33:53,562
If you're familiar with English alphabet
and you know how to read,

469
00:33:54,313 --> 00:33:56,193
- the answer to your question is...
- That's us!

470
00:33:56,690 --> 00:33:59,068
Is there anything we can help you with?

471
00:34:00,778 --> 00:34:02,297
I'm Wade Montalban.

472
00:34:02,321 --> 00:34:03,614
I need your help.

473
00:34:04,490 --> 00:34:07,701
One of our Photography Club members died.

474
00:35:09,722 --> 00:35:10,722
It's still warm.

475
00:35:12,099 --> 00:35:13,225
It smells sweet.

476
00:35:23,116 --> 00:35:26,113
Today is her birthday, isn't it?

477
00:35:26,509 --> 00:35:29,594
Why don't we play a game
to commemorate this day?

478
00:35:30,968 --> 00:35:31,968
M.

479
00:35:40,627 --> 00:35:41,920
He's challenging me.

480
00:35:59,021 --> 00:36:03,442
I'm curious as to why you came here
to fetch us instead of the campus police?

481
00:36:07,154 --> 00:36:08,906
I read your blogs.

482
00:36:09,364 --> 00:36:12,534
And I found out
you've solved a lot of cases.

483
00:36:14,369 --> 00:36:15,369
This one

484
00:36:15,788 --> 00:36:17,664
can you solve this case?

485
00:36:19,541 --> 00:36:20,541
Wait.

486
00:36:20,626 --> 00:36:22,628
What makes you say it's murder?

487
00:36:23,337 --> 00:36:26,840
Doesn't it look like self-harm at first?

488
00:36:27,007 --> 00:36:28,926
Serena and I go way back.

489
00:36:29,301 --> 00:36:31,178
She thinks too highly of herself.

490
00:36:31,595 --> 00:36:32,595
That's why

491
00:36:33,305 --> 00:36:35,808
she couldn't have killed herself.

492
00:36:36,391 --> 00:36:37,643
Does she like drinking tea?

493
00:36:39,269 --> 00:36:40,269
What kind?

494
00:36:41,480 --> 00:36:42,940
I know she's not into tea.

495
00:36:43,440 --> 00:36:45,234
I've never even seen her drink tea.

496
00:36:45,692 --> 00:36:47,778
We don't even keep tea
in the photography room.

497
00:36:50,572 --> 00:36:54,076
Earlier, you said you found her like that.

498
00:36:55,369 --> 00:36:58,580
Could you tell us how this really happened?

499
00:37:02,835 --> 00:37:05,212
Which one should we choose for our poster?

500
00:37:07,005 --> 00:37:08,005
- Wait.
- This.

501
00:37:08,423 --> 00:37:09,423
Oh, gosh.

502
00:37:11,343 --> 00:37:13,887
Serena, I'll just be a sec.

503
00:37:14,388 --> 00:37:15,782
- Is it okay?
- Hurry!

504
00:37:15,806 --> 00:37:17,846
- Hurry up. Hurry up.
- I'll be right back. Promise.

505
00:37:18,142 --> 00:37:20,894
Don't go sneaking off
to the canteen, okay?

506
00:37:31,296 --> 00:37:34,381
When I got back,
she was already covered in blood.

507
00:37:38,787 --> 00:37:39,787
Serena?

508
00:37:40,664 --> 00:37:42,249
Serena!

509
00:37:43,797 --> 00:37:45,507
Help!

510
00:37:52,676 --> 00:37:54,011
Lori, Loki,

511
00:37:54,303 --> 00:37:56,180
are you guys magnets for bad luck?

512
00:37:56,638 --> 00:37:57,638
Chief,

513
00:37:58,265 --> 00:38:00,767
I think you should pay attention
to the teacups.

514
00:38:02,066 --> 00:38:03,066
Okay.

515
00:38:03,476 --> 00:38:04,248
We'll take it from here.

516
00:38:04,272 --> 00:38:09,943
We'll keep you updated on this case
and on Justin Ruiz as well.

517
00:38:17,659 --> 00:38:18,659
Come in.

518
00:38:21,663 --> 00:38:22,663
Get this.

519
00:38:23,332 --> 00:38:24,809
Here.

520
00:38:24,833 --> 00:38:28,170
- Oh, there you go. Just keep writing.
- Give me the rest of those papers too.

521
00:38:29,296 --> 00:38:30,857
Have you ever wondered

522
00:38:30,881 --> 00:38:36,220
why those two were targeted
by Moriarty, or one of his agents?

523
00:38:37,054 --> 00:38:38,054
I mean..

524
00:38:38,388 --> 00:38:42,410
What does he gain from killing
an aspiring basketball player

525
00:38:42,434 --> 00:38:44,603
and a Photography Club member?

526
00:38:45,729 --> 00:38:46,897
I don't know.

527
00:38:48,899 --> 00:38:50,442
But these two cases

528
00:38:51,151 --> 00:38:53,195
have one element in common.

529
00:38:55,155 --> 00:38:56,281
The teacups.

530
00:38:57,574 --> 00:39:00,827
His motive still escapes me.

531
00:39:02,079 --> 00:39:03,497
Maybe he has one,

532
00:39:04,998 --> 00:39:06,250
or maybe he doesn't.

533
00:39:07,084 --> 00:39:08,168
Motive?

534
00:39:09,419 --> 00:39:10,419
Who?

535
00:39:14,466 --> 00:39:15,842
Good afternoon.

536
00:39:16,385 --> 00:39:18,971
Chief Gareth sent over

537
00:39:19,930 --> 00:39:21,616
the fingerprint analysis results

538
00:39:21,640 --> 00:39:23,809
from the teacups
found at the crime scenes.

539
00:39:26,728 --> 00:39:29,189
Thank you, Officer Montreal.

540
00:39:30,857 --> 00:39:34,945
Chief said to reach out
if you need anything else.

541
00:39:35,737 --> 00:39:37,173
That's all. I'll get going now.

542
00:39:37,197 --> 00:39:38,615
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

543
00:39:42,619 --> 00:39:46,456
There are no other fingerprints found
on the teacups

544
00:39:47,207 --> 00:39:48,851
or the pair of scissors

545
00:39:48,875 --> 00:39:51,503
except for the victims.

546
00:39:53,588 --> 00:39:58,135
The campus police
consider these as suicidal cases.

547
00:39:59,052 --> 00:40:02,931
Unless, evidence suggests otherwise.

548
00:40:03,598 --> 00:40:05,100
Whoever is behind this

549
00:40:06,310 --> 00:40:07,769
did a clean job.

550
00:40:19,406 --> 00:40:20,449
Belladonna!

551
00:40:20,782 --> 00:40:21,782
Huh?

552
00:40:22,451 --> 00:40:23,493
Belladonna.

553
00:40:26,747 --> 00:40:29,875
Traces of Belladonna
were found in the teacup.

554
00:40:30,792 --> 00:40:32,294
And on the victim's body.

555
00:40:33,837 --> 00:40:35,255
What's Belladonna?

556
00:40:48,977 --> 00:40:51,748
Belladonna is a poisonous plant

557
00:40:51,772 --> 00:40:56,610
that has been used for medication
since ancient times.

558
00:40:57,402 --> 00:40:59,529
It also goes as a sinister name,

559
00:41:00,113 --> 00:41:01,448
the devil's berries.

560
00:41:01,990 --> 00:41:03,658
And when ingested,

561
00:41:03,825 --> 00:41:09,247
it can also cause vivid hallucinations
and deliriums.

562
00:41:09,790 --> 00:41:11,083
And some use it

563
00:41:12,334 --> 00:41:13,835
as a recreational drug.

564
00:41:14,503 --> 00:41:18,423
Hallucinations? Delirium? That's why!

565
00:41:18,548 --> 00:41:19,633
Exactly!

566
00:41:20,050 --> 00:41:24,054
The culprit did not need
to touch the victim's body

567
00:41:24,971 --> 00:41:26,014
to kill them.

568
00:41:27,432 --> 00:41:31,853
All he had to do
was to offer them a cup of tea.

569
00:41:32,187 --> 00:41:34,499
And once the poison kicks in

570
00:41:34,523 --> 00:41:39,861
it induces hallucinations
that drive them to hurt themselves.

571
00:41:41,488 --> 00:41:44,282
The culprit makes a suggestion,

572
00:41:44,741 --> 00:41:47,077
and the victim will do whatever he says.

573
00:41:51,706 --> 00:41:53,667
Come on, jump.

574
00:42:00,382 --> 00:42:02,968
Come on, jump.

575
00:42:44,551 --> 00:42:45,552
Actually,

576
00:42:45,927 --> 00:42:48,513
it's much more clever than hypnosis.

577
00:42:49,055 --> 00:42:52,350
And there's a chance
that suggestions won't work.

578
00:42:52,893 --> 00:42:54,311
And if that happens,

579
00:42:54,811 --> 00:42:57,856
the poison will do its job
and still kill the victim.

580
00:42:58,690 --> 00:43:00,650
Our culprit is creative.

581
00:43:01,443 --> 00:43:05,447
His choice to use
such an ingenious trick proves it.

582
00:43:06,156 --> 00:43:09,367
He probably didn't want to see someone
dying in a boring way.

583
00:43:11,411 --> 00:43:12,411
Sorry,

584
00:43:13,330 --> 00:43:15,624
that's a bit of information overload.

585
00:43:15,916 --> 00:43:16,916
Okay.

586
00:43:17,334 --> 00:43:18,460
Let's take a break.

587
00:43:19,669 --> 00:43:21,713
I'm gonna grab some coffee
from the cafeteria first.

588
00:43:22,589 --> 00:43:23,589
Do you want one?

589
00:44:01,378 --> 00:44:02,629
Here's your coffee.

590
00:44:03,672 --> 00:44:05,423
Be careful, it's hot.

591
00:44:06,550 --> 00:44:07,551
You know

592
00:44:08,510 --> 00:44:13,098
looks like there's a strong chance
our theories are right.

593
00:44:13,848 --> 00:44:18,937
But if the culprit handed
the teacups to the victims,

594
00:44:19,604 --> 00:44:22,857
how come there were no fingerprints
on them?

595
00:44:24,150 --> 00:44:25,735
He could've used another trick.

596
00:44:27,404 --> 00:44:28,464
We need to think about it

597
00:44:28,488 --> 00:44:30,532
if we want to prove our point
to the police.

598
00:44:33,952 --> 00:44:35,036
Tissue.

599
00:44:36,288 --> 00:44:37,455
That's it!

600
00:44:38,540 --> 00:44:41,585
The culprit handed them
the teacups with a tissue,

601
00:44:41,918 --> 00:44:43,753
which is why there were no fingerprints.

602
00:44:44,921 --> 00:44:46,691
Whoever the culprit is,

603
00:44:46,715 --> 00:44:49,134
they're really good
at covering up their tracks.

604
00:44:50,468 --> 00:44:51,886
Not necessarily.

605
00:44:52,679 --> 00:44:54,139
The first crime was messy.

606
00:44:55,140 --> 00:44:57,910
The culprit didn't expect
anyone to interfere

607
00:44:57,934 --> 00:44:59,269
before carrying out the crime.

608
00:45:00,228 --> 00:45:01,771
He was almost got caught

609
00:45:02,272 --> 00:45:03,648
by other students.

610
00:45:04,816 --> 00:45:07,777
The second case, however,

611
00:45:08,737 --> 00:45:10,614
was almost flawless.

612
00:45:11,364 --> 00:45:13,700
He left no trace of his crime

613
00:45:15,285 --> 00:45:16,870
except for that teacup.

614
00:45:20,749 --> 00:45:21,958
What about Catherine?

615
00:45:22,459 --> 00:45:24,461
Her case might be connected to this.

616
00:45:28,214 --> 00:45:29,424
Catherine no!

617
00:45:30,884 --> 00:45:32,761
I don't think so.

618
00:45:33,386 --> 00:45:36,264
There's a big gap
between her and the next victims.

619
00:45:37,349 --> 00:45:41,936
That's why I truly believe
that hers is an isolated case.

620
00:45:44,022 --> 00:45:46,775
These next two cases are connected.

621
00:45:47,942 --> 00:45:51,863
They were victimized on the same day,
and they were even classmates.

622
00:45:51,888 --> 00:45:53,181
So what do you think of Leo?

623
00:45:53,410 --> 00:45:54,911
That's why,

624
00:45:55,988 --> 00:45:59,193
I think, this guy is not guilty.

625
00:45:59,599 --> 00:46:04,687
It just so happened that he was meeting
his girlfriend that day.

626
00:46:05,377 --> 00:46:07,796
I've been trying to figure out
the motive since earlier.

627
00:46:12,175 --> 00:46:14,552
M wants to send a message to me today

628
00:46:15,804 --> 00:46:17,472
on Rhea's birthday.

629
00:46:18,688 --> 00:46:20,898
He wants to make sure that I receive it.

630
00:46:23,136 --> 00:46:25,347
But since the teacup accidentally broke,

631
00:46:25,855 --> 00:46:28,400
the culprit needs to make another kill

632
00:46:28,566 --> 00:46:32,570
to ensure that I got the message
the second time around.

633
00:46:33,279 --> 00:46:34,406
Therefore,

634
00:46:34,823 --> 00:46:36,825
it just so happened
that Serena became the victim,

635
00:46:37,492 --> 00:46:39,828
and Wade was the unlucky witness.

636
00:46:40,829 --> 00:46:46,292
So if Leo and Wade are both innocent,

637
00:46:47,794 --> 00:46:51,089
then the real culprit is

638
00:46:51,756 --> 00:46:53,007
Daniel Geronimo.

639
00:46:53,675 --> 00:46:57,679
Wow, you actually got
the name right for once!

640
00:47:04,686 --> 00:47:05,979
Impressive.

641
00:47:07,981 --> 00:47:11,901
I know you can solve this puzzle, Loki.

642
00:47:15,029 --> 00:47:18,116
Looks like the warning to me was right.

643
00:47:18,442 --> 00:47:22,070
Once you got the police report,

644
00:47:22,454 --> 00:47:26,040
you'd know I did all this

645
00:47:26,541 --> 00:47:30,462
and, more importantly, what I used.

646
00:47:31,004 --> 00:47:33,798
I have your scandal.

647
00:47:34,549 --> 00:47:36,801
And if you don't drink this,

648
00:47:37,886 --> 00:47:40,430
I'll make sure it gets out.

649
00:47:52,358 --> 00:47:53,401
Who are you?

650
00:47:54,068 --> 00:47:55,528
What are you doing here?

651
00:47:55,820 --> 00:47:59,032
It doesn't matter who I am.

652
00:47:59,991 --> 00:48:01,242
Stay away from me.

653
00:48:02,076 --> 00:48:05,973
What matters is I know

654
00:48:05,997 --> 00:48:10,376
about your secret relationship
with Mr. Olinares.

655
00:48:10,835 --> 00:48:12,086
What are you talking about?

656
00:48:12,420 --> 00:48:14,523
I have evidence

657
00:48:14,547 --> 00:48:19,469
that you two checked into a motel.

658
00:48:19,844 --> 00:48:24,182
So if I were you, I'd just drink this.

659
00:48:25,225 --> 00:48:26,643
Because if you don't,

660
00:48:27,602 --> 00:48:30,998
I'll leak the video of you two.

661
00:48:31,022 --> 00:48:37,111
And everyone will see your scandal.

662
00:48:38,279 --> 00:48:40,341
Is that all I have to do?

663
00:48:40,365 --> 00:48:41,991
I just have to drink that?

664
00:48:42,492 --> 00:48:43,827
Simple!

665
00:48:43,993 --> 00:48:49,499
Just drink this,
and I won't do what I said.

666
00:48:51,125 --> 00:48:52,919
And Catherine...

667
00:48:53,503 --> 00:48:56,339
You both thought she wasn't connected,

668
00:48:57,131 --> 00:48:59,300
but you were wrong.

669
00:49:00,093 --> 00:49:02,929
She just wanted revenge

670
00:49:03,137 --> 00:49:07,141
and to frame Leo, so she did it.

671
00:49:08,101 --> 00:49:10,353
I made her drink the tea too.

672
00:49:19,320 --> 00:49:20,822
Go jump.

673
00:49:22,615 --> 00:49:24,784
Stab yourself,

674
00:49:25,368 --> 00:49:27,245
using scissors.

675
00:49:54,731 --> 00:49:56,858
For a murder suspect,

676
00:49:57,400 --> 00:49:58,902
you're pretty cocky.

677
00:50:01,112 --> 00:50:02,780
You're not Moriarty.

678
00:50:03,114 --> 00:50:04,240
He's a coward.

679
00:50:05,283 --> 00:50:08,745
He hides behind lackeys like you.

680
00:50:09,162 --> 00:50:14,542
It's not time yet, Loki,
for him to show himself to you.

681
00:50:16,544 --> 00:50:17,545
I see.

682
00:50:18,046 --> 00:50:21,883
Can I send him a gift?

683
00:50:22,425 --> 00:50:26,095
Like a pen or something.

684
00:50:36,564 --> 00:50:43,363
Don't. Don't do anything you'll regret.

685
00:51:15,645 --> 00:51:17,021
Are these for us?

686
00:51:18,272 --> 00:51:20,942
You want to murder us
the same way you did the others, huh?

687
00:51:23,903 --> 00:51:28,783
If I wanted to kill you,
I would've done it outright.

688
00:51:29,242 --> 00:51:31,285
But Moriarty doesn't want that.

689
00:51:31,995 --> 00:51:35,206
He doesn't even want a scratch on you.

690
00:51:36,207 --> 00:51:38,167
He's so overprotective of me.

691
00:51:38,876 --> 00:51:40,795
What is he, my girlfriend or something?

692
00:51:43,214 --> 00:51:45,758
This isn't for the two of you.

693
00:51:46,509 --> 00:51:51,472
Sorry, I didn't bring another cup
for your friend.

694
00:51:54,726 --> 00:51:56,811
This is for the two of us.

695
00:51:58,187 --> 00:51:59,772
And what if I don't choose?

696
00:52:01,107 --> 00:52:02,984
What if I just walk out the door?

697
00:52:04,235 --> 00:52:06,279
Or what if I just knock you out right now?

698
00:52:12,243 --> 00:52:14,746
You can try,

699
00:52:15,079 --> 00:52:20,209
so you'll find out
I've got two people waiting outside.

700
00:52:21,335 --> 00:52:26,025
And I'm sure you know
what we can do to you

701
00:52:26,049 --> 00:52:28,885
if you make the wrong move.

702
00:52:38,603 --> 00:52:40,855
What do you think you're doing?

703
00:52:41,105 --> 00:52:42,106
Sit!

704
00:52:43,316 --> 00:52:44,316
Sit.

705
00:52:48,571 --> 00:52:50,031
Let go of me!

706
00:52:50,865 --> 00:52:53,576
I'm not going to kill you, Loki.

707
00:52:54,035 --> 00:52:59,624
You'll just watch your partner
bleed out in front of you.

708
00:53:01,626 --> 00:53:03,669
What makes you think I care about her?

709
00:53:04,378 --> 00:53:08,049
I could just walk away from this room
without getting any scratch.

710
00:53:32,657 --> 00:53:33,908
Stop! Stop!

711
00:53:38,621 --> 00:53:41,040
I thought you didn't care.

712
00:53:44,502 --> 00:53:48,631
Can your conscience handle it, Loki?

713
00:53:48,965 --> 00:53:55,638
Can you handle someone close to you
getting dragged into this again?

714
00:53:56,264 --> 00:53:57,264
Huh?

715
00:54:01,352 --> 00:54:02,478
Now, sit!

716
00:54:19,954 --> 00:54:20,954
Now

717
00:54:21,414 --> 00:54:23,207
let's have a drinking game.

718
00:54:24,375 --> 00:54:29,881
Moriarty wants to test
how good you really are at deduction.

719
00:54:30,631 --> 00:54:34,343
So we're going to play a drinking game.

720
00:54:36,721 --> 00:54:40,641
One of them contains belladonna.

721
00:54:41,475 --> 00:54:46,147
And the other one is just regular tea.

722
00:54:46,647 --> 00:54:48,357
I'll let you choose.

723
00:54:48,900 --> 00:54:53,529
And once you've chosen one,
we drink at the same time.

724
00:54:56,240 --> 00:54:58,826
Do you mind if I sniff
the scent of these teas?

725
00:54:59,118 --> 00:55:01,787
Go ahead, be my guest.

726
00:55:21,390 --> 00:55:25,019
Better pray you chose the right cup.

727
00:55:25,770 --> 00:55:27,730
Let the game begin.

728
00:55:29,649 --> 00:55:35,196
Let's see who walks out
of this room alive.

729
00:55:56,759 --> 00:55:58,469
I have one question for you.

730
00:55:59,512 --> 00:56:02,890
Since this might be our last conversation
we would ever have,

731
00:56:03,391 --> 00:56:07,770
I wanna know why Moriarty
is so obsessed with me.

732
00:56:08,104 --> 00:56:09,647
Mind telling me the reason?

733
00:56:11,023 --> 00:56:13,609
When your former partner died,

734
00:56:14,402 --> 00:56:19,115
he was upset
that you suddenly vanished off his radar.

735
00:56:20,074 --> 00:56:21,551
But he got fired up again

736
00:56:21,575 --> 00:56:28,708
when he heard you were involved
in the case at the chemistry lab.

737
00:56:30,668 --> 00:56:33,504
And the many other cases you meddled in.

738
00:56:35,506 --> 00:56:39,260
So I returned to his radar after that case?

739
00:56:39,677 --> 00:56:44,432
You meddled in his business again
this academic year.

740
00:56:45,266 --> 00:56:46,892
One of the recent ones

741
00:56:47,101 --> 00:56:54,317
was our kidnapping of the math prodigy
found in an abandoned school building.

742
00:56:54,942 --> 00:56:57,403
Our client ran into a problem.

743
00:56:57,611 --> 00:57:02,867
So we found a way
to make his wish come true,

744
00:57:03,117 --> 00:57:06,829
to get that man out of his way.

745
00:57:27,725 --> 00:57:30,895
You're just like us, at Q.E.D.?

746
00:57:32,063 --> 00:57:36,108
You also solve problems,
but in a deadly way.

747
00:57:37,568 --> 00:57:44,241
We just grant the wishes
of students who need our help.

748
00:57:44,992 --> 00:57:46,619
And for the right price,

749
00:57:47,703 --> 00:57:51,582
we can do anything for them.

750
00:57:52,249 --> 00:57:54,919
If they want someone taken out,

751
00:57:55,211 --> 00:57:58,547
something stolen,

752
00:57:58,756 --> 00:58:02,635
or information obtained,

753
00:58:03,719 --> 00:58:07,431
all of it, every request they make,

754
00:58:08,182 --> 00:58:10,410
we pass it on to Moriarty,

755
00:58:10,434 --> 00:58:14,647
and he decides what we do next.

756
00:58:15,648 --> 00:58:17,858
Just like his fictional namesake.

757
00:58:18,859 --> 00:58:21,028
He's the mastermind,

758
00:58:22,071 --> 00:58:23,823
and you're the ones who carry it out.

759
00:58:24,782 --> 00:58:28,536
Or he can be the director,

760
00:58:29,537 --> 00:58:31,372
and we're the actors.

761
00:58:32,392 --> 00:58:34,310
Have you ever seen him in person?

762
00:58:35,126 --> 00:58:37,035
Do you know who Moriarty is?

763
00:58:37,376 --> 00:58:38,752
Or what he looks like?

764
00:58:39,713 --> 00:58:42,091
Or what his voice sounds like?

765
00:58:43,384 --> 00:58:46,554
I'm just a pawn on his chessboard.

766
00:58:48,139 --> 00:58:52,685
Only the high-ranking members
know who he is.

767
00:59:36,437 --> 00:59:38,230
Lorelei!

768
00:59:38,898 --> 00:59:39,898
Rhea

769
00:59:41,150 --> 00:59:42,150
is that you?

770
00:59:42,234 --> 00:59:43,777
What are you doing here?

771
00:59:45,154 --> 00:59:46,154
Hey.

772
00:59:46,405 --> 00:59:47,573
Wake up, sleepy head.

773
00:59:49,158 --> 00:59:50,159
Loki!

774
00:59:50,826 --> 00:59:51,637
You're alive!

775
00:59:51,661 --> 00:59:53,597
Good thing you're awake.
How are you feeling?

776
00:59:53,621 --> 00:59:55,974
My subconscious said
that you're also crying?

777
00:59:55,998 --> 00:59:57,625
Why would I cry over you?

778
00:59:57,666 --> 01:00:00,770
Anyway, take care, you guys.
Loki. Especially you, Lorelei.

779
01:00:00,794 --> 01:00:03,273
Wait, do you suspect the professor?

780
01:00:03,297 --> 01:00:04,507
Morayta

781
01:00:05,299 --> 01:00:06,943
is the Filipino version of Moriarty.

782
01:00:06,967 --> 01:00:10,513
Here's Daniel Geronimo's autopsy report.

783
01:00:12,056 --> 01:00:13,658
Just checking if I'm still alive?

784
01:00:13,682 --> 01:00:15,494
Or are you here to finish the job?

785
01:00:15,518 --> 01:00:19,313
It's ironic, because I did warn you,
stop looking for M.
